  <result aggregation-status="1" type="1">
   <title>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">Annual Output Results</narrative>
   </title>
   <indicator ascending="0" measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Output Indicator</narrative>
    </title>
    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. A fully functional new system for Certifying Internal Auditors in the public sector 
2. Continuous professional development program and career path for Internal Auditors in the public sector developed and launched 
3. Professional organisations implementing IA Certification. 
4. A regular consultation mechanism between the CHU and professional organisations established 
5. At least two tertiary education institutions selected 
6. Improved technical capacity of the CHU expressed through improved efficiency and effectiveness in meeting the obligations deriving from their scope of responsibility</narrative>
    </description>
    <baseline year="2018">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. An inappropriate system for Certifying Internal Auditors in the public sector is currently in place Professional development programs and career path for Internal Auditors in the public sector do not exist at present.
2. No consultation mechanism between the CHU and professional organisations exists
3. Tertiary education institutions are not implementing a curriculum on Internal Control</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2019-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2019-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">-The new system for certifying internal auditors in public sector is fully functional by the end of 2019
- Continuous professional development program and career path for IAs in the public sector developed and launched by the end of 2019
- At least five professional organizations implementing IA Certification training programs meeting the minimum requirements and standards identified by the end of 2019
- At least two tertiary education institutions expressing interest in introducing a new subject on Internal Control and Audit identified in 2019</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Professional organization identified
- Tertiary education institution to introduce new subject on internal control and internal audit identified
- Analysis of the optimal number of internal auditors in public sector conducted</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2020-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2020-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">- New educational programme on internal audit and internal control introduced in one tertiary institution
- Continuous professional development program for internal auditors introduces
- Legislative act necessary to allow the positive spill over of internal auditors from private sector introduced</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Undergraduate and Master courses in Accounting and Auditing upgraded to include new subject on Internal Audit and new study materials
- Rulebook on professional developmen of Internal Auditors adopted 
- IA in public sector received training in new iinternal audit methodologies: Performance Audit and IT Audit
- New exam for certified internal auditor in public sector piloted in order to include the self-study material developed by the project</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
